Ideally, we could use two for loops to check odd numbers for prime, and even numbers using another two for loops for divisors.

One for loop can check for prime numbers but not divisors. If we use two for loops, one is for prime numbers and another should be for divisors. How to check divisors?

## Solution 

```
package prime;
/**
 * Created by Gaurav Sharma on 1/21/18.
 */
public class Prime { 
	public static boolean isPrime(int num) {
		if(num < 1 || num > 100) return false;
		for(int i = 2; i <num ; i++){
            if(num % i > 0) return false; 
        }
		return true;
	}
	public static int[] getPrimeNums(int[] primes){
		int n = primes.length;
        for(int i =0 ; i <= n ; i++){

            if(!isPrime(i)) primes[n] = i;
        }
	}
    public static void main(String[] args){
       int[] primes = new int[1000000];
       getPrimeNums (primes);
       for (int i = 0; i < primes.length; i++) 
       		System.out.print(primes[i]+" ");
    }
}
```
